**The TL;DR:** A 0.50ct round diamond costs 13–18% more than a 0.49ct with zero visual difference on the finger. Jewelers call this the magic size premium. Blue Nile prices for a 0.50ct G-VS2 GIA Excellent run ~$790. A 0.49ct same grade runs ~$680. You're paying $110 extra for a number nobody sees.

The 0.5ct milestone exists for marketing, not optics. A 5.2mm diamond (0.50ct) and a 5.1mm diamond (0.49ct) cannot be distinguished on a hand without calipers. The half-carat psychological trap costs buyers hundreds of dollars every year.

---

